'''''Space M+A+X''''' is a 1986 video game published by [[Final Frontier Software]].

==Gameplay==
''Space M+A+X'' is a game in which the moon is colonized and mined.<ref name="CGW35"/>

==Reception==
Johnny L. Wilson reviewed the game for ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'', and stated that "MAX is a remarkable and fascinating simulation. It should be played by everyone who is even remotely interested in space exploration and/or hard science fiction. It should be savored by those of us who enjoy economic simulations."<ref name="CGW35">{{cite magazine |last=Wilson |first=Johnny L. |title=M+A+X-imum Concentration: Modeling the Future Using Space M+A+X |magazine=Computer Gaming World |date=March 1987 |volume=1 |issue=35 |pages=22â€“24, 62}}</ref>

